## Finding hamming distance between two input strings
## position i in k-mers p1, p2,...,pk and q1,q2,...,qk is a mismatch if pi != qi
## number of dismatch is called the Hamming Distance and is denoted HammingDistance(p,q)

##Input
# Seqp = scan(file.choose(), what = "")
# Seqq = scan(file.choose(), what = "")
##test
Seqp = ""
Seqq = "
"
Seqp = strsplit(Seqp, "")[[1]]
Seqq = strsplit(Seqq, "")[[1]]
length = length(Seqp)
Count = 0
for (i in 1 : length){
  Count = ifelse(Seqp[i] != Seqq[i], Count + 1, Count)
}
print(Count)